So basically we need 2 commands to provide permission chmod and chown. chown is use for change the owner and chmod use for change of group. So means every file on directory we hav 3 permission groups e.g Owner, Group and other.
d rwx rwx r-w
d (directory in case of folder)  rwx (Owner) rwx (Group)  r-x (All User)
1.	For Change owner: chown (new owner name) filename --- this is use for change file owner only
To change file owner and group: sudo chown saqib:saqib filename
2.	Chmod (change mode) r= 4, w=2 and x=1
Chmod 664 filename
While common permission as below
644- file basline
755 â€“ directory basline
400 â€“ key pair 


